The paper discusses a method to increase the interpretability and reproducibility of deep neural networks (DNNs) by incorporating the idea of feature selection with controlled error rate. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG) as it deals with DNNs and feature selection. Additionally, the paper also mentions the use of deep learning in both supervised and unsupervised machine learning, which further supports the likelihood of it belonging to cs.LG. The paper also mentions the lack of interpretability in deep learning methods, which suggests that it could also belong to the sub-category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The use of DNNs in image processing and computer vision is also mentioned, which suggests that it could belong to the sub-category of Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the architecture of DNNs, which suggests that it could belong to the sub-category of Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE). Finally, the paper mentions the use of simulated and real data sets, which suggests that it could belong to the sub-category of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS).
